    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix integer overflow in EMM attach accept processing\n\n### Summary\nThe `emm_proc_attach_accept` function in Attach.c was vulnerable to integer overflow when processing the number of tracking areas (n_tais) and equivalent PLMNs (n_eplmns). These parameters were passed as `int` but stored in `Byte_t` fields which can only hold values 0-255. Large or negative values would cause wraparound or truncation.\n\nThis fix adds validation to prevent integer overflow and ensures proper bounds checking.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/EMM/Attach.c`: Added parameter validation for n_tais and n_eplmns to prevent integer overflow when assigning to Byte_t fields. Invalid values are clamped to safe ranges and errors are logged.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain network conditions where the MME sends an abnormally large number of TAI or EPLMN entries, the UE would incorrectly process these values due to integer overflow. This could lead to:\n- Incorrect TAI list processing\n- Memory corruption in adjacent data structures\n- Unexpected behavior in mobility management\n\nThe issue is triggered when n_tais or n_eplmns values exceed 255 or are negative, causing wraparound when stored in the uint8_t n_tais/n_plmns fields.\n"
}